PAST MEDICAL HISTORY
1) Crohn's colitis - primarily involving the ascending colon. She does suffer from some arthritis.
2) Primary sclerosing cholangitis, stable. Clotting factors normal, bilirubin normal, no ascites. Has extrahepatic PSC with dominant stricture of the right hepatic duct and common hepatic duct.
3) Cardiac status, stable.
4) Anemia, on Iron and VB12 therapy.
5) GERD, on treatment.
6) History of depression/anxiety, on treatment.
7) G3P3.
PAST SURGICAL HISTORY
1) Cholecystectomy 2007.
2) Eye surgery, per PPI.
3) Tonsillectomy.
4) Hysterectomy.
5) Bladder surgery, per PPI.
6) Recent ERCP, biliary sphincterotomy, cholangioscopy, biliary duct biopsies, biliary brush cytology. Balloon dilation done at that time. Cytology negative for malignancy.

